{
    "name": "Detective",
    "type": "alien",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "Detectives pursue and apprehend those deemed criminals, leaving matters of judgment and incarceration to the courts to handle. They specialize in subduing their foes, often considering lethal tactics to be unprofessional or beyond their jurisdiction. Most detectives work within the law, but some work outside or even against it, particularly in areas where government authorities can\u2019t be counted upon to uphold the law."
        },
        {
            "name": "Investigators",
            "type": "section",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Interstellar Species",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Interstellar Species pg. 170",
                        "alt": "Interstellar Species pg. 170",
                        "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq02d4w?Starfinder-Interstellar-Species"
                    },
                    "page": 170
                }
            ],
            "html": "Investigators uncover secrets and sift truth from lies. This often places investigators on the side of the law, but when the powers that be are corrupt, investigators might find themselves labeled vigilantes or ostracized. Yet they aren\u2019t easily discouraged, and can become relentless foes."
        }
    ],
